 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T012 (unified Source Registry schema)
 
 - Twelfth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S1-P02 (Source Registry single source truth), one task per run. Goal: cover the existing five boards and China A0-A2 and distinguish official evidence from discovery. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; no crawl behaviour, worker, or D1 changed (schema-only). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: schemas/source_registry.schema.json (draft-07: source identity with a unique source_id, the authority enum china_official/intl_official/journal/preprint/media/search/aggregator, an authority_level restricted to A0/A1/A2 for china_official, official_evidence, and enable/health/cursor fields enabled/health_status/cursor/cadence, with conditional rules), tools/validate_source_registry.py, and source_registry.sample.json (7 sources across the five boards + China A0/A1/A2 + a discovery aggregator/media). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T012/test-results/registry_schema_tests.txt): the valid sample is VALID; a china_official source with authority_level A3 is INVALID and one missing the level is INVALID (China official levels outside A0/A1/A2 fail); a media source marked official_evidence=true is INVALID (media can never be official evidence); and a duplicate source_id is INVALID. This is the schema base for DRIFT-FACT-006 (source-truth drift); the actual migration of live sources is T013 and the compiler is T014. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
